parameters:
Town Mayor: Hmm... I'm in a bind... Can someone
lend me a hand?
(Seems like you're in some kind of trouble...)
Would you like to hear the story?

Town Mayor: Oh, Ayako-san. The preparations for
the sake offering are complete. Are you ready to
join us now?

Town Mayor: I-Is that so... Well, that's
unfortunate... I was hoping you would drink it
while it's still hot...

Town Mayor: Oh, Ayako-san! The preparations are
complete!

Town Mayor: We are about to perform the
ceremony... but before that, may I have a little
chat?

Town Mayor: First, let me explain the origin of
this ceremony. It is based on a legend passed down
in this shrine.

Town Mayor: Once upon a time, this land was
thriving with hunting of animals, and the majority
of the villagers made a living from it, leading to
moderate prosperity.

Town Mayor: And those few who couldn't engage in
hunting resorted to farming, but the hunters
mocked and looked down upon them as cowards.
Naturally, a rift began to form between the two
groups.

Town Mayor: However, suddenly terrifying monsters
began to spread in the forest, causing the animals
to flee and the hunters to suffer from extreme
poverty, not knowing where their next meal would
come from...

Town Mayor: And so, a renowned shrine maiden
arrived there and taught the hunters the value of
working together with the farmers to cultivate
crops.

Town Mayor: They spread fertilizer in the fields,
nurtured the soil, taught them how to use tools,
sowed seeds, and harvested...! The hunters who
understood the joy of agriculture started
cooperating with the farmers, and the village
flourished overnight.

(Is this Rei's story...? She's surprisingly doing
something decent, huh)

Town Mayor: And so, we honor that shrine maiden,
turning her story into a ritual, which has been
passed down to this day.

Town Mayor: And now, the contents of this
ritual... *gulp*
Wha...! Why did it turn out like that?

Town Mayor: This is a crucial scene where the
shrine maiden meticulously teaches the hunters how
to use farming tools.

Town Mayor: Don't worry, I didn't say you have to
do the real thing. If you just touch it with your
hand, it'll be over in no time.
W-Well... if it's with my hand...

Town Mayor: As expected, Ayako-san, you're quick
to understand!! Come on, the men are waiting
inside! Go in, go in.

Town Mayor: Now, it's finally time for the grand
finale of the ceremony. Are you ready?

Town Mayor: This ceremony will finally come to an
end this time.

Town Mayor: Oh my, it would have been impossible
to come this far without your help, Ayako-san. I
am truly grateful.

Um... By the way, what exactly do we have to do
for the final part? It's probably something lewd
again, isn't it?
Town Mayor: Hmm, well, that's the general idea.

Sigh... Well, I guess there's no helping it... ♡
We used our hands and mouths before, so this is
finally the main event, right?

Well, this is also part of the ceremony, right? If
we use protection, I don't mind. It's not because
I couldn't do it last time or anything like that.
At this point, I genuinely want to engage in this
ceremony... not just have sex...

Town Mayor: It seems like you're misunderstanding
something, but the content this time is the same
as last time.

Huh?!! We're not going to be denied again...! I
mean...! Are we not going to do it...?

Town Mayor: Hmm? Even if you say not going to do
it, I'm not sure what you're referring to.

Town Mayor: Anyway, I kindly ask that you
absolutely refrain from doing anything unnecessary
other than what you did last time.

Town Mayor: Oh, it's already this late. Come on,
don't keep the men waiting inside.

W-Wait! L-Look! Boys are interested in a girl's
body, right? I-I can let them touch me if you
want!

Town Mayor: There is no need for inappropriate
emotions during the ceremony. Now then, I kindly
ask for your cooperation.
Town Mayor: Hmmm... Mmm... I see...

By the way, I wonder where Rei-san usually hangs
out?... Or is it okay to leave the shrine
unattended?

I wonder what ghosts usually do? There are so many
things I don't know.
Do you want to watch Rei's Daily Life Part 1?

Lately, you've been disappearing a lot... I wonder
where you're really wandering around...
Would you like to watch Rei's Daily Life Part 2?

Lately, Rei-san has been smiling mischievously
from time to time... I wonder if something fun
happened?
Would you like to watch Rei's Daily Life Part 3?

After the event ends, if you press the Q key, you
can hear Ayako's soliloquy about that event.

Basically, it doesn't affect the game progress if
you don't listen to it, but she might whisper
something that could lead to hints for capturing.

Also, be aware that if you fall asleep at home or
listen to the event-related soliloquy
once,\c[2]she won't whisper it again.\c[0] So
please be careful if you want to hear all the
conversations.
